  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why my Jio sim barcode shown redeemed?",
  "response": "If your Jio SIM barcode is shown as \"redeemed,\" it typically means that the QR code or barcode associated with your SIM activation process has already been used to complete the activation. Here are some possible reasons and solutions for this issue:\n\n### Possible Reasons:\n1. **Already Activated**: The SIM card has already been activated using the barcode, so it\u2019s marked as \"redeemed.\"\n2. **Duplicate Attempt**: Someone might have mistakenly or fraudulently used the barcode to activate a different SIM.\n3. **System Glitch**: There could be a technical issue or glitch in the Jio system that marked the barcode as redeemed prematurely.\n\n### What to Do:\n1. **Check SIM Activation Status**:\n   - Visit the [Jio SIM activation status page](https://www.jio.com/selfcare) or use the MyJio app to check if your SIM is already activated.\n   - If it\u2019s activated, proceed to use your SIM normally.\n\n2. **Contact Jio Customer Care**:\n   - If your SIM is not activated but the barcode is shown as redeemed, contact Jio customer care at **198** or **199** (toll-free) for assistance.\n   - Explain the issue and provide your SIM number and other details to verify your account.\n\n3. **Visit a Jio Store**:\n   - If customer care is unable to resolve the issue, visit the nearest Jio store with your SIM card, documents, and proof of purchase (if applicable) for manual activation.\n\n4. **Verify Purchase Source**:\n   - If you purchased the SIM from a retailer, ensure it was a legitimate Jio distributor. In case of any discrepancies, report it to Jio.\n\n5. **Request a Replacement SIM**:\n   - If the barcode is irredeemable and your SIM cannot be activated, Jio may issue a replacement SIM card.\n\nAlways ensure you keep your purchase receipt and SIM card details safe until the activation process is complete.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
